         <p>Here's a list of the operations we do most when using oXygen, with a brief reminder of
            how to perform them.</p>
         <div>
            <head>Operations on a complete document</head>
            <list type="gloss">
               <label>Create a new TEI XML document</label>
               <item>
                  <list>
                     <item>Click the New icon at top left, or select New from the File menu, or type
                        CTRL-N to open the New dialog box</item>
                     <item>If you want to use one of the predefined TEI schemas, choose
                           <ident>Framework Template</ident>, then <ident>TEI P5</ident>, and then
                        choose the schema you want, for example <ident>Bare</ident>,
                           <ident>Lite</ident>, <ident>all</ident> etc. </item>
                     <item>If on the other hand you want to use a personalised schema you have made
                        yourself, then choose <ident>New Document</ident>, then <ident>XML
                           Document</ident>, and click on the <ident>Customize</ident> button at the
                        bottom. In the dialog which thenm opens, you must specify where the schema
                        you want to use is to be found, for example by navigating to the
                           <ident>out</ident> folder if it is locally stored, choosing tjhe right
                        schema file, and clicking the Open button</item>

                     <item>In either case, click on the <ident>Create</ident> button at the bottom.
                        oXygen displays a minimal template for your chosen TEI schema. </item>
                     <!--
                  <list xml:lang="fr">
                     <item>Cliquez sur l'icône Nouveau en haut à gauche (ou sélectionnez Nouveau du menu
                     Fichier, ou tapez CTRL-N) pour ouvrir la boîte de dialogue Nouveau</item>
                  <item>Si vous souhaitez utiliser un des schemas TEI predefinis, choisissez <ident>Cadre des modèles</ident>, ensuite <ident>TEI P5</ident>, puis
                     selectionnez la modele que vous souhaitez, par ex. <ident>Bare</ident>, <ident>Lite</ident>, <ident>all</ident> etc. </item><item>Si par contre vous souhaitez utiliser un schema personnalise que vous avez creer vous meme, choisissez <ident>Document nouveau</ident>, ensuite <ident>XML Document</ident>, et cliquer sur le bouton <ident>Customize</ident> en bas. Dans le dialog qui s'affiche, il faut specifier la location du schema que vous desirez, par ex en naviguant au dossier <ident>out</ident> ou il est stocke en local</item>
                 
                  <item> Cliquez sur le bouton <ident>Créer</ident> en bas. oXygen affiche un document TEI
                     minimal que vous allez compléter.</item>
-->
                  </list>
               </item>
               <label>Process an ODD</label>
               <item>
                  <list>
                     <item>Open a valid ODD file</item>
                     <item>In the <ident>Document</ident> menu, choose <ident>Transformation</ident>
                        -> <ident>Configure Transformation Scenario(s)</ident>, or type CTRL-MAJ-C,
                        or click the appropriate icon on the toolbar. </item>
                     <item>A list of available transformations is displayed. Tick the box next to
                        those you want to apply: for ODD, the most useful are probably TEI ODD XHTML
                        and TEI ODD to RELAXNG Compact</item>
                     <item><graphic url="../Graphics/oxy-scenarios.png" height="7cm"/>
                     </item>
                     <item>Click the <ident>Apply Assciated</ident> button to start the
                        transformations</item>
                     <item>By default, the XHTML will be displayed using your default browser, while
                        an RNC output will be saved in a folder called <ident>out</ident>, which
                        oXygen will create in the current directory if necessary </item>
                  </list>
               </item>
               <!--Lancez oXygen et ouvrez le fichier <ident>cartes-tei.odd</ident> qui se trouve dans
                     votre dossier <ident>Travaux</ident>
                  </item>
                  <item>Dans le menu <ident>Document</ident> sélectionnez <ident>Transformation</ident> ->
                     <ident>Configurer Les Scenarios de Transformation</ident>, ou tapez CTRL-MAJ-C, ou
                     cliquez l'icône sur la barre d'outils. </item>
                  <item>Les transformations possibles sont affichées. Déroullez pour trouver celles qui
                     concernent les ODD et cochez les cases qui vous interessent, par ex: TEI ODD
                     XHTML et TEI ODD to RELAXNG Compact</item>
                  <item><graphic url="../Graphics/oxy-scenarios.png" height="7cm"/>
                  </item>
                  <item>Cliquez sur le bouton <ident>Appliquer Associé(s)</ident> pour lancer les
                     transformations.</item>
                  <item>Si tout va bien, la sortie XHTML s'affiche dans le navigateur, et la sortie RNC sera
                     enregistrée dans un dossier <ident>out</ident>
                  </item>
               </list>-->
               <label>Associate a TEI XML file with a schema</label>
           <item><list>    <item>The schema association for a TEI document is usually set up when the document is created; if this is not done, oXygen will by default assume your file is to be validated against TEI All. To change this, select <ident>Schema --> Associate schema</ident>  from the <ident>Document</ident>  menu.</item><item>Navigate to the schema file and press Open</item><item>oXygen inserts a processing instruction at the start of the document. </item><item>If there are several such PIs, oXygen uses the last one. </item></list></item>
                  <!--  <item>Pour utiliser votre nouveau schéma, il suffit de sélectionner <ident>S Associate chema ->
                  Sélectionner un schéma</ident> sur le menu <ident>Document</ident> et puis de naviguer
                  jusqu'au fichier <ident>out/cartes-tei.rng</ident></item>-->
               <label>Associate a TEI XML file with a stylesheet</label>
               <item>This can be done in two ways: <list><item></item></list></item>
            </list>
         </div>
         <div>
            <head>Operations on the content of an XML document:</head>
            <list>
               <label>Insert text from a file</label>
               <item>
                  <list>
                     <item>Put the cursor at the point in your document where you want the text to be inserted</item><item> Choose <ident>File -> Insert File</ident> from the
                           <ident>Document</ident> menu (<emph>not</emph> the <ident>File</ident>
                        menu!) </item>
                     <item> Navigate to the file whose contents you wish to insert </item>
                     <item>Press Open</item>
                  </list></item>
               <label>Tag a stretch of text</label>
               <item><list>
                     <item>Select and highlight the stretch of text you want to tag with the
                        mouse.</item>
                     <item>Type CTRL-E or choose <ident>XML Refactoring -- Surround with
                           Tags</ident> from the <ident>Document</ident> menu</item>
                     <item>Select the tag you wish to use from the drop down menu (type its first
                        letter to scroll the list rapidly) </item>
                  </list></item>
               <label>Split a tagged element in two</label>
               <item><list>
                     <item>Put the cursor at the place where you want to split the element. </item>
                     <item>Type ALT + SHIFT + D or choose <ident>XML Refactoring -- Split
                           Element</ident> from the <ident>Document</ident> menu</item>
                  </list></item>
               <label>Untag an element</label>
               <item><list>
                     <item>Put the cursor anywhere inside the element you wish to untag. </item>
                     <item>Type ALT + SHIFT + X or choose <ident>XML Refactoring -- Delete Element
                           Tags</ident> from the <ident>Document</ident> menu</item>
                  </list></item>
               <label>Change the tagging of an element </label>
               <item>
                  <list>
                     <item>Put the cursor inside the start- or end-tag of the element you
                        wish to rename. </item>
                     <item>Choose <ident>XML Refactoring -- Rename Element</ident> from the
                           <ident>Document</ident> menu</item>
                     <item>Type the new name you want and indicate whether which occurrences you
                        want to change</item>
                     <item>Press OK to make the changes </item>
                  </list></item>
            </list>
         </div>
         <div>
            <head>Operations on non-XML documents</head>
            <list type="label">
               <label>Open and convert a docx file</label>
               <item><list>
                     <item>In oXygen, use the usual Open dialog to select the docx file</item>
                     <item>A window opens to the left of the main screen headed "Archive Browser".
                        It shows the file structure of the docx archive.</item>
                     <item><graphic url="navigateur-1.png" height="4cm"/></item>
                     <item>Click the blue key next to the folder called word to see the contents of
                        this folder</item>
                     <item><graphic url="navigateur-2.png" height="4cm"/></item>
                     <item>Select the file called document.xml and double click to open it (may take
                        a few moments if the file is large)</item>
                     <item><graphic url="document-word.png" height="4cm"/></item>

                     <item>With the <ident>document.xml</ident> file open in your main editing
                        window, select <ident>Transformation -> Configure Transformation
                           Scenario(s)</ident> from the <ident>Document</ident> menu. Or type
                           <code>CTRL-SHIFT-C</code>. Or click the little spanner icon (this one :
                           <graphic url="spanner.png" height="7mm"/>) </item>
                     <item>For the default DOCX to TEI conversion, check the little box next to DOCX
                        TEI P5 and press the <ident>Apply Associated</ident> button </item>
                     <item><graphic url="configurer-1.png" height="4cm"/></item>
                  </list>
                  <!--<item> A new window opens at the
                     bottom of the screen in which oXygen displays messages relating to the conversion
                     process ; you may safely ignore these. </item>
                 <item>In the main editing window, you should now see a TEI-conformant document. (Choose
                     Source > Indenter le document from the Document menu, or type CTRL-MAJ-P or click the
                     Indent button (this one: <graphic url="indent.png" height="7mm"/>) if it is displayed
                     as a single line on the screen) Scroll down to see how the Word styles have been
                     converted. </item>
                  <item><graphic url="converted-1.png"  height="6cm"/></item>
                  <item>Note that many of the paragraphs have a rend attribute. The values of this
                     attribute correspond with the Word style used in the original docx file. You can use
                     these values to make a more intelligent conversion.</item>
               </list>
               <list>
                  <item>Close the tab labelled Test_tous-styles-TEI-P5.xml to return to the window
                     containing document.xml, your source Word document.</item>
                  <item>Click on the spanner again to reopen the Configurer Scenarios de Transformation
                     dialog and this time click the Edit button at the bottom. This will enable you to
                     reconfigure the bdefault conversion process.</item>
                  <item>You can't modify a built in configuration scenario, so oXyGen offers to make a
                     copy for you to play with. <graphic url="yesno.png" height="2cm"/>. Press <ident> Oui.</ident>
                  </item>
                  <item>The <ident>editer le scenario ANT </ident> is displayed to enable you to configure
                     your new version of the transformation scenario. <graphic url="editer-scenario-1.png" height="4cm"
                     /></item>
                  <item>Let's begin by changing its name to something sensible: change "DOCX TEI P5
                     copier" to "DOCX TEI P5 Oulipo" for example.  Then press the Parametres tab to see
                     what else can be modified.</item>
                  <item><graphic url="editer-scenario-2.png" height="4cm"/></item>
                  <item>This dialog allows us to change the default input and output paths for this
                     transformation and also to specify a <term>profile</term>. The TEI Stylesheet package
                     included with oXygen supplies a small number of predefined sets of customized
                     stylesheets called profiles. You can use or modify an existing profile to get the
                     effects you want in your own project (not covered here). In this exercise, we will
                     use the Oulipo profile. </item><item>Select the word Profile and  press the Edition button. </item>
                  <item/>
                  <item><graphic url="modifier-parametre.png" height="4cm"/></item>
                  <item>Add the word oulipo in the box labelled Valeur and press Accepter to return to the
                     Editer le scenario Ant dialog. Press Accepter again.</item>
                  <item>Your new transformation scenario should now be available in the Configurer
                     Transformation Scenario dialog. Check the little box next to it, and uncheck the box
                     next to the default Scenario.</item>
                  <item><graphic url="configurer-3.png" height="4cm"/></item>
                  <item>This OULIPO profile includes rules to handle the Word styles which were simply
                     passed through as values for the rend attribute in the default transformation
                     scenario.  (These rules are written in XSLT; we don't tell you here how to write
                     them). Run the transformation again, by pressing Appliquer associes.  You should see
                     something rather different this time...</item> -->
               </item>
               <label>Open and display an image file</label>
               <item>You can use the usual Open dialog to open an image file in JPG or PNG or TIFF
                  formats.The image opens in a separate window which you can dock within the main
                  editing area, resize, or move around or pin, using the window controls. You can't
                  however zoom or otherwise process the image: for that you need to install a plugin
                  such as WHATEVER ITS CALLED </item>
            </list>
         </div>
